<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4688459>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. — Fossil Brachyura from Monségur (Gironde, France): A, Planobranchia simplex (Remy, 1960) n. comb., cast of holotype, MNHN R03839,dorsal carapace;B,Planobranchia laevis (Lőrenthey,1909) n. comb.,cast of holotype,IMDASlf.Nr.25520/2005 (dorsal carapace); C, Branchioplax? ballingi Remy in Remy & Tessier, 1954, cast of holotype, MNHN R03793, fragmental dorsal carapace; D, Liocarcinus heintzi n. sp., holotype, R03778, dorsal carapace; E, F, Pleolobites erinaceous Remy, 1960, casts of holotype, MNHN R03782 (E), and MNHN R03781 (F). Scale bars: 1 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4688459/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

